{# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Audit User Message Template
   Variables: channel, channel_constraints (json), audience, audience_tone,
              rules_text, content
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}
Audit the following content against the brand rules provided.

TARGET CHANNEL: {{ channel }}
CHANNEL CONSTRAINTS: {{ channel_constraints }}

TARGET AUDIENCE: {{ audience }}
AUDIENCE TONE GUIDANCE: {{ audience_tone }}

BRAND RULES:
{{ rules_text }}

CONTENT TO AUDIT:
{{ content }}

Return a JSON object with:
- "violations": array of violation objects, each with:
  - "original_text": exact text span from the content
  - "issue_title": short description of the issue
  - "rule_section": section reference (e.g. "§3 — Prohibited Words")
  - "rule_id": rule identifier (e.g. "RULE-3.1")
  - "explanation": why this violates the rule
  - "severity": "critical" | "high" | "medium" | "low"
  - "suggested_fix": specific replacement text or action
  - "blocks_publishing": true/false
- "summary": one-paragraph summary of the audit findings

Be thorough. Check every sentence. Only cite rules from the provided list.
